<subSubSection pageId="45" pageNumber="46" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="45.[151,1436,151,752]" pageId="45" pageNumber="46">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[201,336,476,500]" inLineHeading="true" pageId="45" pageNumber="46" reason="1">Etymology.</emphasis>
The specific name is derived from the Latin prefix 
<emphasis box="[929,952,477,500]" italics="true" pageId="45" pageNumber="46">a-</emphasis>
(absent) and 
<emphasis box="[1108,1168,477,500]" italics="true" pageId="45" pageNumber="46">spina</emphasis>
(spine), in reference to the absence of the outwardly-directed spines on the posterior margin of the vinculum in the male genitalia which otherwise are characteristic of this species-group.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
